      "source": [
        "## Treating the null values"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WqxO6Sg9ZGD7"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Since, Markdown columns are explaining the marketing campaign details, also, the percentage null values are above 50%, so we will impute the null values with 0**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "1yt7GkxIt4qv"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Imputing the null values in markdown columns with 0\n",
        "data.iloc[:,4:9]=data.iloc[:,4:9].fillna(0)"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FUCcQh60X-6Y"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Treating the null values in cpi and unemployment columns by imputing with 'forward fill' method because it is a huge data and we are having only 7% missing values in these two columns.**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BIgvq-uKvh9i"
      },
      "source": [

      "source": [
        "**Since, there are 81 departments for each store we will group the departments on the basis of the frequency of purchases from that department. Here we are grouping the departments into five types namely:'rare','less frequent','moderately frequent','very frequent','most frequent'**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "gjilBX8qkL1B",
        "outputId": "142118f8-845d-404d-edca-3c5eb4e89381"
      },
      "source": [
        "print(round(data['Dept'].value_counts(normalize=True),4).describe(percentiles=[0.20,0.40,0.60,0.80]))\n",
        "dep = pd.DataFrame(data['Dept'].value_counts(normalize=True).values,columns=['Dept_freq'])\n",
        "dep['Dept'] = data['Dept'].value_counts(normalize=True).index\n",
        "data_n = pd.merge(data,dep,on='Dept',how='inner')\n",
        "labels = ['rare','less frequent','moderately frequent','very frequent','most frequent']\n",
        "bins = [0,0.0115,0.0136,0.0149,0.0153,np.inf]\n",
        "data_n['Dep_type'] = pd.cut(data_n['Dept_freq'],bins=bins,labels=labels)\n",
        "data_n = data_n.drop('Dept_freq',axis=1)"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [

      "source": [
        "**Percentage Outliers in the Numerical Columns**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "csgRnV4JMwlq",
        "outputId": "f772022c-8e37-4649-f07f-68f8e0a9e46c"
      },
      "source": [
        "for col in num_col:\n",
        "  count=0\n",
        "  q1,q3 = data_n[col].quantile([0.25,0.75])\n",
        "  iqr = q3-q1\n",
        "  uw = q3+1.5*iqr\n",
        "  lw = q1-1.5*iqr\n",
        "  for i in data_n[col]:\n",
        "    if i<lw or i>uw:\n",
        "      count+=1\n",
        "  print('Percentage of outliers in '+col+' ={}'.format(count/data_n[col].shape[0]))"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",

        "**From the above results we observe that p-value < 0.05(alpha), thus the test rejects null Hypothesis, that is the data is not normal. Since, the data is not normal we have to use non parametric test to check whether the means of each of these samples are equal or not.**"

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "UEZlBKYNTZ0B"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Since, the pvalue < 0.05 (alpha), means we reject null hypothesis thus, we can say that there is a significant difference in the weekly sales due to department type.**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6tetoAY07rmB"
      },
      "source": [
        "**From the above graph we can infer that:**\n",
        "\n",
        "1.   We can see that there is not much difference in weekly sales in any type of departments when there is holiday or not, except the departments which are moderately visited as the outliers are more on holidays. That means, during particular holidays people tend to by more products from moderately visited departments.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "y-A6Ub_PyoxK"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Statistical test to prove if there is a significant difference in the average weekly sales due to promotional markdowns**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_j51Yu2Ay5yU"
      },
      "source": [
        "mark_grp = data_n_train['Weekly_Sales'].groupby(data_n_train['markdown'])"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "z66yQNEvy47y"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Checking the normality of the samples**\n",
        "\n",
        "**Hypothesis**\n",
        "\n",
        "    H0: The data set is normal\n",
        "    H1: The data set is not normal"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "d57iPDRMzWqy",
        "outputId": "b7a7ed49-3646-4608-d106-8c5c5fddd319"
      },
      "source": [
        "for i in range(data_n_train['markdown'].nunique()):\n",
        "  print('markdown = {}'.format(i))\n",
        "  print()\n",
        "  print('P-value = {}'.format(st.shapiro(mark_grp.get_group(i))[1]))\n",
        "  print('***'*40)"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "markdown = 0\n",
            "\n",
            "P-value = 0.0\n",
            "************************************************************************************************************************\n",
            "markdown = 1\n",
            "\n",
            "P-value = 0.0\n",
            "************************************************************************************************************************\n"
          ],
          "name": "stdout"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ENwMwxLW0cO1"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Inference: From the above results we can see that the p-value < 0.05(alpha), thus we reject the null hypothesis, that is the data in samples are not normal.**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MI827tVx3iY0"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Hypotheis for checking equalence of means between samples:**\n",
        "\n",
        "    H0: The means of the samples are equal\n",
        "    H1: The means of the samples are not equal"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "DABzpylc3tqM",
        "outputId": "ec2cb645-bd86-41e3-e5ed-4ce42e78e770"
      },
      "source": [
        "print('P-value = {}'.format(st.mannwhitneyu(mark_grp.get_group(0),mark_grp.get_group(1))[1]))"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "P-value = 0.09197362788125363\n"
          ],
          "name": "stdout"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Sz3kraT13su7"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Inference: From the above results we can observe that p-value>0.05(alpha), which means the test failed to reject null hypothesis. Thus, we can conclude that there is no significant difference in the weekly sales due to promotional markdowns run by the Walmart stores across the US.**"
      ]
    },

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ghs7hM0zL0Zt"
      },
      "source": [
        "# removing the outliers from the columns of both train dataset except 'Weekly Sales' column \n",
        "\n",
        "## removing outliers from the \n",
        "for col in df_new_train.columns.drop(['Weekly_Sales','IsHoliday','markdown','Week']):\n",
        "  q1,q3 = df_new_train[col].quantile([0.25,0.75])\n",
        "  iqr = q3-q1\n",
        "  lw = q1-1.5*iqr\n",
        "  uw = q3+1.5*iqr\n",
        "  df_new_train[col] = df_new_train[col].apply(lambda x: lw if x < lw else x)\n",
        "  df_new_train[col] = df_new_train[col].apply(lambda x: uw if x > uw else x)\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },

      "cell_type": "code",

        "# Modeling for the whole data set"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BjPaoLApqlCv"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Doing logarithmic transformation to make the data less skewed\n",
        "## We will not consider logarithmic transformation of columns: ISHoliday,Type, Markdown,and Dep_type because these columns are encoded and thus logarithmic tranformation won't be a right choice to deal with this data\n",
        "\n",
        "for col in df_new_train.columns.drop(['IsHoliday','Type','markdown','Dep_type']):\n",
        "  df_new_train[col] = np.log(df_new_train[col])"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {

        "# Model Building"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "qdzGlVz77SWh"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Assigning indepndent and Dependent variables**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BEPnvnkZ2_SU"
      },
      "source": [
        "# assigning the independent and the dependent variables\n",
        "x = df_new_train.drop('Weekly_Sales',axis=1)\n",
        "y = df_new_train['Weekly_Sales']"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nV88X1jF7ZWx"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Building Base Model"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 597
        },
        "id": "DXMuiFk22_PN",
        "outputId": "61c41bdf-1834-494a-d311-cf0b100687dd"
      },
      "source": [
        "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
        "xc = sm.add_constant(x)\n",
        "model = sm.OLS(y,xc).fit()\n",
        "model.summary()"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/html": [
              "<table class=\"simpletable\">\n",

              "</tr>\n",
              "<tr>\n",
              "  <th>Model:</th>                   <td>OLS</td>       <th>  Adj. R-squared:    </th>  <td>   0.367</td>  \n",
              "</tr>\n",
              "<tr>\n",
              "  <th>Method:</th>             <td>Least Squares</td>  <th>  F-statistic:       </th>  <td>2.708e+04</td> \n",
              "</tr>\n",
              "<tr>\n",
              "  <th>Date:</th>             <td>Wed, 31 Mar 2021</td> <th>  Prob (F-statistic):</th>   <td>  0.00</td>   \n",
              "</tr>\n",
              "<tr>\n",
              "  <th>Time:</th>                 <td>13:42:06</td>     <th>  Log-Likelihood:    </th> <td>-8.0160e+05</td>\n",
              "</tr>\n",
              "<tr>\n",
              "  <th>No. Observations:</th>      <td>420212</td>      <th>  AIC:               </th>  <td>1.603e+06</td> \n",
              "</tr>\n",
              "<tr>\n",
              "  <th>Df Residuals:</th>          <td>420202</td>      <th>  BIC:               </th>  <td>1.603e+06</td> \n",
              "</tr>\n",
              "<tr>\n",
              "  <th>Df Model:</th>              <td>     9</td>      <th>                     </th>      <td> </td>     \n",
              "</tr>\n",

              "  <th>Covariance Type:</th>      <td>nonrobust</td>    <th>                     </th>      <td> </td>     \n",
              "</tr>\n",
              "</table>\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mhLU6fhnVhtd"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Modeling**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nuJW4VpJfjel"
      },
      "source": [
        "def model_res(algo,x_train=x_train,x_test=x_test,y_train=y_train,y_test=y_test):\n",
        "  algo.fit(x_train,y_train)\n",
        "  cof_df = pd.DataFrame(algo.coef_,index=x_train.columns,columns=['Coefs_lr'])\n",
        "  print(cof_df)\n",
        "  print()\n",
        "  print('Intercept = {}'.format(algo.intercept_))\n",
        "  print('***'*40)\n",
        "  y_pred_train = algo.predict(x_train)\n",
        "  y_pred_test = algo.predict(x_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "  print('Evaluation of the model on Train data set')\n",
        "  print('R-squared = {}'.format(r2_score(y_train,y_pred_train)))\n",
        "  print('RMSE = {}'.format(np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_train,y_pred_train))))\n",
        "  print('MAE = {}'.format(mean_absolute_error(y_train,y_pred_train)))\n",
        "  print('***'*40)\n",
        "  print('Evaluation of the model on Test data set')\n",
        "  print('R-squared = {}'.format(r2_score(y_test,y_pred_test)))\n",
        "  print('RMSE = {}'.format(np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred_test))))\n",
        "  print('MAE = {}'.format(mean_absolute_error(y_test,y_pred_test)))"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    }
  ]
